  <TITLE>move</TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function</TYPE>
  <DATE> 2002</DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="move"> 
   move, translate,  a graphic entity and its children.
  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
    <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>move(h,xy) </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
    <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>move(h,xy,&quot;alone&quot;) </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
    <PARAM_INDENT>
      <PARAM_ITEM>
        <PARAM_NAME>h</PARAM_NAME>
        <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: a handle, the handle of the entity to move.</SP>
        </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
      </PARAM_ITEM>
      <PARAM_ITEM>
        <PARAM_NAME>xy</PARAM_NAME>
        <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: an array <VERB>[dx,dy]</VERB> which gives the translation
  vector to apply.</SP>
        </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
      </PARAM_ITEM>
      <PARAM_ITEM>
        <PARAM_NAME>&quot;alone&quot; </PARAM_NAME>
        <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: string keyword (optional).</SP>
        </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
      </PARAM_ITEM>
    </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
    <P>
    This routine can be used to apply a translation to a graphics entity.
    If the entity has children, they will be also translated.</P>
    <P>
    Given the keyword <VERB>&quot;alone&quot;</VERB> , only the specified entity needs to be redraw. 
     It must specially be used with the <VERB>pixel_drawing_mode</VERB> 
     property of the figure entity (see draw objects under
    <VERB>&quot;xor&quot;</VERB> drawing mode).</P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
